## {{ drug.molecular_formula }}

Colloidal Silicon Dioxide contains not less than 99.0 per cent and not more than 100.5 per cent of SiO2, calculated with reference to the ignited substance.

Identification: About {{ drug.strength }} gives the reaction of silicates.

pH: Between 3.5 and 5.5, determined in a {{ drug.dosage_form }} of {{ drug.strength }} in {{ drug.strength }} of carbon dioxide-free water

Chloride: To 1.{{ drug.strength }} add a mixture of {{ drug.strength }} of 2M nitric acid and {{ drug.strength }} of water, heat on a water-bath for 15 minutes, shaking frequently, dilute to {{ drug.strength }} with water if necessary, filter and cool. The filtrate complies with the limit test chlorides  (250 ppm).

Arsenic: To 2.{{ drug.strength }} contained in a round-bottomed flask add {{ drug.strength }} of 3M hydrochloric acid and heat under a reflux condenser for 30 minutes. Cool, filter with the aid of suction and transfer the filtrate to a 100-ml volumetric flask. Wash the filter with several portions of hot water and add the washings to the volumetric flask. Cool, dilute to volume with water and mix. To 50.{{ drug.strength }} of the {{ drug.dosage_form }} add {{ drug.strength }} of hydrochloric acid; the resulting {{ drug.dosage_form }} complies with the limit test for arsenic, ppm).

Heavy metals: Not more than 25 ppm, determined by Method D on {{ drug.strength }} of a {{ drug.dosage_form }} prepared in the following manner. Suspend 2.{{ drug.strength }} in sufficient water to produce a semi-fluid slurry and dry at 140o. When the dried substance is white, break up the mass using a glass rod, add {{ drug.strength }} of 1M hydrochloric acid, boil gently for 5 minutes, stirring frequently with the glass rod, centrifuge for 20 minutes and filter the supernatant liquid through a membrane filter. To the residue in the centrifuge tube add {{ drug.strength }} of 2M hydrochloric acid and {{ drug.strength }} of water, boil, centrifuge for 20 minutes and filter the supernatant liquid through the same membrane filter. Wash the residue with small quantities of water, combine the filtrates and washings and dilute to 50.{{ drug.strength }} with water. To 20.{{ drug.strength }} of the {{ drug.dosage_form }} add {{ drug.strength }} of L-ascorbic acid and {{ drug.strength }} of strong ammonia {{ drug.dosage_form }}, neutralise with 2M ammonia and dilute to {{ drug.strength }} with water. Use lead standard {{ drug.dosage_form }} (1 ppm Pb) to prepare the standard.

Loss on ignition: Not more than 5.0%, determined on 0.{{ drug.strength }} by igniting at 900o in a platinum crucible for 2 hours,

Assay: To the residue obtained in the test for Loss on ignition add 0.{{ drug.strength }} of sulphuric acid and sufficient ethanol (95%) to moisten the residue completely, add {{ drug.strength }} of hydrofluoric acid and evaporate to dryness on a hot plate at 95o to 105o, avoiding loss from sputtering. Wash the sides of the dish with {{ drug.strength }} of hydrofluoric acid, evaporate to dryness in a well-ventilated hood, ignite at 1000o, allow to cool in a desiccators and weigh. The difference between the weight of the final residue and that of the residue obtained in the test for Loss on ignition represents the amount of SiO2 in the amount of the substance taken for the test for Loss on ignition.
